Apr 13 2008 	Good quality good service good price	With 7-star this and 5-star that hotels plastered all over Dubai, it was refreshing to find a small, modern hotel that wasn't intimidated by its swankier competitors. The standard of rooms was very high, housekeeping was very regular, the overall service standards professional and there's plenty of choice at breakfast. The hotel pool/sun deck is just big enough for the size of the hotel, though you're not going to be taking much more than a dip in the pool as it's not built for laps. The gym and sauna facilities are well maintained and the staff there are friendly and helpful. The hotel is in a great location for local restaurants and for walking through the city, though it will take you a good 25 minutes to get down to the Spice Souk at a moderate pace. It's not so great if you're looking for a beach-based holiday as the beaches are about half and hour away or more (but then again, almost any journey by car involves getting caught in the Dubai traffic, so half an hour is fairly standard to get anywhere). If there's one thing the hotel could do better, it would be to improve its concierge skills -- they're a bit inconsistent and local knowledge could be better. Overall we got good quality and good service for a good price. We'd definitely go back.	
Apr 12 2008 	Great Hotel	We stayed at the Rimal Rotana Suites in Deira for three nights. We arrived at about 3 30 am and realised we should have booked for that night, as well as the three we had booked, but the staff at reception were very helpful, and they gave us a two bedroom suite so that we could get some sleep. We then had to change to the room we had booked later that day. The hotel has recently been renovated, with the reception/lobby/dining area being quite contemporary. There is an area with four laptops for guests to access the internet. I paid 20dhs (AUD$5.90) for 1 hour and that can be used over a 24 hour period, although there are several other choices depending on the time required. Other staff in the dining room and on the door were also very helpful and accommodating. Our room was a good size, with a kitchenette, bar fridge, king size bed (very comfortable), plenty of hanging space in the wardrobe, as well as an iron and ironing board. You can self cater, but we found the food in the dining room really good and reasonably priced. The hotel is not in the real tourist area, but we enjoyed exploring the streets and shops, as well as taking a taxi to the Deira Shopping Mall (10dhs/AUD$2.95 + 5dhs tip-our choice). We didn't get the hotel staff to arrange any tours as we had already organized our own before we left Australia, but they can if needed. Our only negative comment would be about the smell of cigarette smoke coming into our room under the door, but it was probably more pronounced because we are non smokers. All in all, we would certainly recommend this hotel.	
