Jul 27 2007	What An Excellent Hotel 5* Standard!	We stayed at the rimal rotana suites for a total of 10 nights in a superior twin suite. This hotel was clean, modern and with excellent guest services. The staff at reception, the bell boys and the cleaning staff were amazing, they couldn’t do enough to help you. The transfers were a bargain at 60AED return although he did ask for a tip on dropping us back at Dubai airport, the cheek!! The rooftop pool was quiet all day with about 5 guests at a time but after 6pm it started getting busy due to the cooling temperatures at night. The pool is small but enough! The hotels rooms were clean and modern with all mod. cons including air conditioning (essential in Dubai), LG TV which was huge and climate control. The minibar was expensive with coke cans priced at £3 but this was expected at such services. The hotel was happy for us to have takeaway from Pizza Hut on our first night delivered up to the room with no charge, although we did tip. For two of us we paid a total of £1200 for the Air France flight via CDG (which was easy, and we are only 18 and 15!) and the hotel which was cheap for Dubai. Also, the position is excellent with taxi fares cheap in Dubai we went to the Mall of Emirates around 3 times with the fare at about 16£ return. Traveling by Taxi is the best and safest way although the taxis change their fares in the evening and if you’re stuck in a traffic jam which 10/10 times you will be, as everyone travels by car, you will pay a waiting car at 0.50AED per 2 seconds which can add a large amount to the total fare. Rimal Rotana Suites was all I expected it to be for a 4* hotel!	
