May 9 2007 	Avoid rush hour!	We've just come back from staying at this hotel for three nights. Lovely, clean room with king sized bed. The hotel has obviously been refurbished recently. Great range of food from the buffet breakfast. The pool was a bonus – a great way to end the day. Great if you get the pool to yourself – it's open tnil 10pm, along with the gym and sauna which are also on the top floor. Big supermarket across the road, to the right. Cheap local restaurant across the road. £7 for two people for entree, main and big bottle of water! The airport is nearby, but everything else is a 15-20 minute walk, if you're not travelling during rush hour. It took us an hour to get back back to the hotel one night when we caught a taxi from the marina at 6pm. Budget 50 dirhams for every trip in the taxi. Beware of the extra taxes at the hotel. We booked through lastminute.com so we were covered, but there was a German couple who were shocked to learn that they had to pay an extra 20% when they went to settle their bill.	
