Mar 5 2007	A very pleasant stay	I stayed at this hotel for 17 nights at the end of February/early March.Every one of the staff could not have been more helpful and friendly, and the room was of a decent size and comfortable. Although the kitchen was there, I did not have any use for it. I'm not sure anyway about having a kitchen in the bedroom - how many of us would do that at home - but that's a personal thing.The satellite tv worked fine although some of the stations were a bit 'fuzzy' - a common problem I've found in Dubai over the years. During my stay, wireless internet was being installed for use in the rooms, a good idea as before that the only alternative was antiquated dial-up in the room or a couple of computers in the lobby.A big plus is that the restaurant in the lobby is open 24 hours, and the menu is reasonable. As another poster mentioned, there are other restaurants nearby, including a respected-by-locals one directly across the road. I personally liked the all white and glass aspect of the lobby/reception area. Very clean and airy. There is an outside terrace which is useful for smokers in particular, but there will be much of the year when that would not be an option because of the heat and humidity.There is little to attract westerners in the immediate vicinity, but more tourist-friendly malls are only 10 minutes away, City Centre in particular.No bar, but I discovered a Fiipino nightclub in a hotel behind the Rimal, called Metro Manila. I and my colleagues spent many happy evenings there, with entertainment provided by a couple of impressive groups consisting of musicians and energetic dancers. Decent price for the drinks too.This is certainly a hotel I would return to.	
