Jan 6 2007 	A good value hotel in a less hectic part of Dubai	This is a clean, modern, comfortable hotel in the business district of Deira. Its restaurant is not great, but there are many inexpensive and nice Lebanese, Egyptian, Iraqi and other cuisines a short walking distance from the hotel. Generally the service is good. The rooftop pool is quite small. It's not far from Dubai International Airport and the Deira City Center shopping mall, making the location even more convenient. On days that are not blisteringly hot, you can also walk to the Reef Mall and Al Ghureir Center. You can often book good rates on the Rotana site, Orbitz, Travelocity, and other internet sites.	
